Angola President Picks Manuel Vicente as Successor, Jornal says

-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-09-02T09:02:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/angola-president-picks-manuel-vicente-as-successor-jornal-says.html
Angolan President Jose Eduardo  dos Santos  has picked Manuel Vicente, chairman of state-owned oil
company Sonangol EP, as his successor, weekly newspaper Novo
Jornal reported today, citing an unidentified person in the
ruling party.  Dos Santos, who has ruled  Africa ’s second-biggest oil
producer for over three decades, is to step down either before
next year’s general election or one year after the vote,
according to the Luanda-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
